reviews:
Tej was the gentleman in charge at breakfast and he was excellent. Funny and very attentive to everyone’s needs. Breakfast options were pretty good.

The hotel is clean and cosy plus at a good location. I would stay here again.

We booked this hotel for 2 night this Novembre. The staff was great and polite, the room was clean and provided everything we needed. The free minibar at the reception and in the room was eccellent.
The breakfast was also great, with a good variety of food.
If we return to Paris we Will definetelly book here, the location was marvelous, extremly near the metro line and bus Number 30 which arrives at the tour Eiffel.

Astoria hotel give as a 5 star experience, from the moment we enter the hotel warmed welcome and assisted by one of the receptionist the hospitality of the staff and it feels like home for us. Special mention to Mr. Tej a cheerful guy for being helpful and hospitable. And also special thanks to Merly, william and Sid Thank you for the memorable experience. Indeed, we will stay again in this wonderful hotel.

Best 3 star hotel I’ve been to. The room was very clean and the room was very cute. Only stayed for about a day but it provided everything we needed. Breakfast was great and so was Tej and his service!

Me and my family stayed in for the holidays. The hotel was so clean and nice! I loved my stay there!!! The staff were so friendly and respectful, they made me and my family feel cozy like we were just at home! The rooms were so nice and the food was super delicious. The place was so affordable and neat. They gave great deals and service. The beds were very comfortable and the rooms smelt so great!! Definitely coming back next time!!!

The hotel was super. The service was nice and the workers are accomodating and friendly, especially Tej from the breakfast. We were happy with our stay and it was great experience. This place is highly recommend.

One of the best 3 star hotels we've ever stayed. Room was clean and we loved the snacks, complimentary drinks were also served with some more free snacks. Great breakfast and the staff at the breakfast was super helpful, Tej. He was very welcoming and very friendly. Over all good it was good choice. We enjoyed our stay.

Perfect hotel for our needs. Room was a good for Paris with comfortable beds. Nice oocation with apartment buildings, hotels and shops nearby. It was lovely to see the children going out to school in the morning. Waiter was very friendly and helpful in the breakfast room.The free mini bar was very welcome. Definitely will come
Back

We've been here for the third time, my husband for at least the 10 th time.
Each time it was wonderful.
Small, but clean rooms with free (!) Minibar.
Sumptous breakfast. Extremly friendly staff everywhere.
Familiar atmosphere.
Each time again with pleasure.

This is a comprehensive review of the Hotel, as well as Paris in general.

1. First of all, a big Kudos to the Management of this Hotel. They were awesome. We had payment issues on the last day, and had a flight to catch. The Manager running things there, was really very sweet, helpful and kind, and let us pay later. Not all Hotel Management will be empathetic like that, and we really really appreciate their understanding, and help !
2. The Hotel breakfast is pretty good. Although there is not much variety compared to Asian Hotels, there are eggs, fruits, sausages, breads, one salad, yoghurt etc. Pretty good. Special mention to breakfast staff, like Merly, and Tej, who are extremely sweet, kind, helpful, and hard working !
3. The Breakfast room is open for guests to have their lunch and dinner as well. There is a Microwave oven here which guests can use easily to heat food purchased from Carrefour or Monop Dublin nearby. These 2 stores are very close to the hotel, on both ends of Rue De Moscou, the street the hotel is on. This is extremely convenient, because you get lots of food, wine etc there.
4. The Rooms are extremely small, probably even by Parisian standards. Be prepared. The Hotel provides a basic soap/shampoo and coffee, hot water kettle. No dental kits, unless asked. And no lotion, moisturiser in the rooms.
5. We stayed there for 8 nights. Not all staff are friendly or helpful. Some can be rude and refuse to help you sometimes. We found that with the Reception, and Room cleaning staff. Room cleaning and stock replenishment was also not thorough on many days.
6. There are several metros and bus stops within walking distance of the hotel. So using public transport is easy. We found the buses more convenient. Google Maps is not always 100% reliable in Paris, so do double check.

Now as for Paris itself …
We were awed by the Louvre, Sainte Chapelle, The Moulin Rouge and the Eiffel Tower (especially at night), Montmartre … as well as other tourist attractions.
But here are a few things we thought could be improved, especially given the number of tourists that flock here.
1. There are stairs everywhere, and I mean everywhere ! Lots of them. On the metro, tourist attractions etc. It could be a huge issue for the disabled, as well as those who are older with some mobility issues. We ourselves found it tiresome sometimes. Having a few more escalators, or elevators, at these places, could be immensely helpful to tourists, and Parisians !
2. Toilets, Eateries, and Seats, especially around tourist attractions, could be much improved. Most places don’t have anywhere to sit, just a few sprinkled seats here and there, which get filled up pretty quickly ! You have to walk up the stairs, or down several flights, to get to a toilet, where the queues are often crazy. It’s the same with food outlets. I know tourists flock to Paris anyway, but maybe Paris could be a little kinder to them, since we end up spending so much money there :)
3. There could also be a lot more helpful signs, instructions, and notices in English, for tourists. And Parisians don’t often help, even if they can. For example, we were fined Euro 50 for not stamping our train tickets. We had purchased them on the Versailles train platform, and there was no doorway to walk through to stamp it. It seems that there is a machine somewhere which stamps these tickets, right there on the platform. This is not mentioned anywhere ! Certainly not in English. So even though we bought the tickets properly, we had to pay a fine. We were told we were lucky we just paid one Euro 50, and not 3, for all 3 of us ! It is very clear to anyone here that there is no intent to defraud or cheat them off money, just a stamping technicality, and yet there was no empathy, or understanding, from the ticket inspectors. The intent is not to help.

It was a lovely stay. We were on the 5th floor. It was a small elevator but worked and never had to wait very long. The mini fridge was stocked everyday and made coming back at the end of the day nice to have a cold beverage. The rooms were clean. The staff was nice and helpful-Tej. The hotel is convenient to a few different metro stations and bus stops. The neighborhood was quiet and peaceful. We enjoyed our stay.

Nice coolatmosphere, service and reception were amazing, specially Mr. Tej, cheerful and great service, rooms are clean even though little small. first impression was not that amazing but once you are there it was nice and great exprerience with all the staff and services

Nice hotel with service and reception were amazing, specially Mr. Tej, cheerful. The rooms are clean even though small. impression was not that amazing but once you are there it was nice and great exprerience with all the staff and services

Super friendly staff — especially our breakfast host Tej! We felt so welcomed. He always remembers me and is so friendly. 😄 Tej is the best! I will keep coming back because he is so nice.

The front desk staff also have a great sense of humor and are happy to help you with suggestions for your time in Paris. The rooms are competitively priced and the location is close to Rome metro stop. Easy to get to nearby attractions and a short walk or bus ride to the center. Great hotel!

We stayed in this hotel just to be in this trip in a different area of Paris. The hotel is located near Place Clichy and near Gare St Lazare. The hotel has a modern appeal and rooms are clean and the bed was comfy and clean. The breakfast waiter was really friendly, contrary to the front desk. We will choose this hotel and area for our next visit.

The hotel was lovely, all areas including the room were clean, the staffs were amazing especially TJ. The position of the hotel is also very good. Great value and I highly recommend it if you travel on budget. We will be back.

Decent place, with good metro and bus connectivity. 2-3 metro stations far from Montmartre, decent breakfast spread. Mr. Tej in particular was quite helpful. The room we selected was small but quite smartly designed.

Very nice hotel, good breakfast, very friendly person Tej, spoke and learned every language, it was wonderful experience. I think next when I caming in Paris. I was stay in this hotel. Every day room is cleaning.

The rooms were lovely and so comfortable. The bathroom was large with really good lighting on the mirror. But the highlight for sure was the delicious breakfast and the wonderful staff. They were all so kind and helpful. Tej was especially amazing and helpful. High recommend this hotel if you want to stay on a quiet and cozy street.

TEJ waited on us in the restaurant was wonderful! He was pleasant and helpful. It made our morning happy! Thank you.

The quiche was superb!

The front desk clerk was extremely friendly and helpful.

The room was a bit small but clean and well laid out.

e stayed here for 3 nights. The hotel is located in District 8. There are small supermarkets and convenience stores just around the corner, which is quite convenient. The room is clean, the bed is not very comfortable, not very supportive. The toilet is ok and the water pressure is normal. The beverages in the refrigerator can be drunk freely which is very good. The breakfast guy is very helpful and accomodating in all stuffs even giving direction and tips. Will definitely come back.

The hotel was just okay. It was modernly updated.The room was dated and very small, but clean. The bathroom was nicely updated. The breakfast they served was okay at best. Breakfast was ok and waitress were seem to be little annoying when to be asked for addional service.They said they offered snacks and drinks for late night snacks, that was very limited and the one time I went to get some water only a quarter of a serving was.There really wasn't anything special about this hotel. If I were to go again, I would pick another hotel.

Great location for dining, sightseeing and shopping. The hotel is immaculately clean, the room and lobby bars are nicely supplied. The free breakfast have good selections. Arlene and Merlyn at the dining area are very hospitable, friendly and helpful.

Stayed here with my wife 5-8th may 2023
The metro stop Rome is a 2 min walk from the hotel and is only a couple stops from Charles de Gaulle Etoille which has a couple connections To the main attractions of Paris also can connect to the train to Disneyland from there aswell
Arrived at the hotel the staff were great
The corridors look abit outdated but the rooms clean and were very nice bathroom was also great with a bath/shower
seen some reviews complain about the size not sure what they are like if you have a family but for me and my wife the room size was fine you’re in Paris you won’t be spending much time in the room anyway
Free mini bar that’s topped up daily
Also you get free snacks and drinks at reception croissants/mini muffins etc
On our final day we were able to leave our luggage with reception whilst we got a few more hours until we left for the airport.
If we ever come back to Paris I will definitely be staying here again.

The room was ok as we only slept here but was tired looking and small. Free soft drinks in the fridge were welcome.Decor was nice and attractive.The rooms were not cleaned well during our stay.Breakfast was good and thanks to TJ for letting us eat early because lady named merly was little snobbish when we wanted because she said its too early.Overall nothing to complain about the reception and was helpful

First time in Paris and read some good reviews about this place. It was in a nice place in Paris where it felt safe. A little far to walk but OK to the Eiffel Tower, Museums and shopping areas, but on a nice day a 30 min walk is fine. Not so when raining.

The rooms were small, very, but as expected in Europe. But was very clean. Bathrooms and beds spotless. The bar fridge with free water, orange juice and sparkling water was great and very handy. The breakfast downstairs range wasn’t huge but sufficient and fresh.
Staff were friendly and I sent them an email and asked to them to print some tickets and they did it without a fuss.
There is a chemist down the road which is handy as well a number of patisserie’s around the corner. It is close to Moulin Rouge and also Sacré Coeur ( 20 min walk ).

Would stay again as once you become familiar to a place it’s nice to go back again.

The complimentary drinks in room and snack table in foyer nearly got it to 5 stars.

We had a comfortable but small room at this hotel, located on a pleasant and quiet street in Paris. It’s within short walking distance to several metro stations, so connections to the rest of the city are easy. Beds and pillows were very comfortable. The lift is cute and tiny! Breakfast, along with Tej and his team, were superb and made our stay very enjoyable.
One major downside, unfortunately soundproofing was non-existent. There was no street noise thanks to the quiet road but we could hear our neighbour in the next room doing absolutely everything. This included all of his bodily functions, trips to the bathroom and TV noise until the very early hours of the morning. It was very unpleasant. I advise you to bring earplugs.

Delighted with our stay, the staff was pleasant and had fully informed us in English about places to visit and restaurants to choose from, well decorated room and the prices were very correct for Paris

We had a very pleasant stay at the hotel. A family room means two rooms connected with one and other via a small hall way. We enjoyed a nice continental breakfast and TJ was our waiter. A friendly guy working hard to keep everything clean and available. Giving every customer a warm welcome and if you would like a chat he was your man.

Excellent hotel and staff, always friendly and willing to help, especially the breakfast service with TJ the host!

The hotel’s location is pretty central, you can walk or have easy access to public transportation. Very good restaurants around too

We had a really nice stay in this hotel, location is great, 2 near Metro stations, the street is very quiet so we are always rested after days of exploring. We stayed in a standard double room, had a cute little window, would be nicer if it was facing the street. The hotel is room is small but very clean, happy to have daily free non alcoholic drinks in the room as well. Staff were helpful and we met a nice kababayan ( Merly ), very hospitable and friendly. I will recommend this Hotel to family and friends.

Excellent hotel down a quiet side street. Ideal location for getting about - 5 minutes walk to nearest metro station.
Very clean, beds and towels changed daily (perhaps a bit too frequently).
Staff very friendly and helpful. Especially TJ in the restaurant !
Free mini bar (non-alcoholic) in the room and free drinks and snacks available in the lobby daily from 2pm.
Throughly recommend this hotel but don't expect large rooms, just very adequate for being out and about most of the time. Would definitely return or try another Astotel Hotel elsewhere.

The room was clean, comfortable, and charming. The staff were helpful and made checkin/out an easy processThe Breakfast Room was clean and ample for the amount of people served. We were
amazed at the quality of the food served. Tj was fantastic attendant while we were there and
we feel he made up for a few shortcomings in the dining area. The lady name merly was annoying since we ask her some honey and said to wait while the other lady gave it instantly which was suprising. Anyway hotel was nicely located and well decorated

the breakfast attendant, Arlene. was extra gracious to us. She has a smiling disposition that makes your morning so bright for a good start. An experience that was so welcoming.
Thank you for making us feel at home.
Last night, we came in late and we had to order our food from the uber service, we used the breakfast lounge as our venue. A microwave oven was also available. Water and beverage was free

The hotel is located in the centre of Paris, close to Roma underground station.
Staff is extremely helpful especially a Receptionist Florence,who helped me with planning my trips around Paris. She wrote me down every station in underground to reach my destination.

The whole breakfast staff is awesome. Astoria has a good bfast team, TJ, Merly and everyone. The staff at the reception area are awesome as well. Very helpful. Had a great stay overall. Will surely recommend to others.

Had a great stay here for 3 nights for our honeymoon. Great location, just near Rome station and shopping areas like printemps, Galeries Lafayette are walkable. Staff were very friendly and accommodating too especially the bar and breakfast crew Sid, TJ, meryl? and everyone.

We really liked that they were very generous with their open bar food and drinks in the afternoon til evening. And food from outside are very welcome in the bar. The front desk staff also were very helpful with our needs. Highly recommended!

I enjoyed my stay at this hotel. My vacation was amazing. High-level service, very convenient location , clean and comfortable room, friendly staff, delicious breakfast and very funny and friendly TJ . thanks everyone, girls from reception very helpful, i will come back for sure this hotel only 🙏❤️

The staff at Hotel Astoria are really kind and helpful. Arleen and TJ went above and beyond to provide excellent service and they were personable and funny. They treated us like family which is really appreciated when you’re traveling. Arleen and TJ deserve an increase in wages for providing 5 star excellent service. The reception staff were also excellent with helping answer our questions about our stay and traveling around Paris. Our room was clean and the size was a bit small but sufficient for three people. Also, it’s nice to have a mini fridge in the room that is stocked with complimentary cold drinks. It’s quiet and comfortable to get some rest.

We ate breakfast in the hotel and I found out they also have complimentary snacks and drinks from 2pm to midnight. This was a delightful surprise and their breakfast staff is amazing. There is a variety of food items and the food is delicious. The location is conveniently located close to two metro stations so that makes traveling easier. The little things and the great staff make it worth it and I’m so glad that I booked our stay at Hotel Astoria. I would definitely recommend staying at Hotel Astoria. Thank you to the Hotel Astoria staff for making it a pleasant experience for me and my family.

A true gem in a quiet yet central part of Paris. Excellent value for money, friendly and helpful staff. TJ in particular must be mentioned for his cheery and efficient service in the dining room. The free mini bar and afternoon snacks are a real bonus. We even had Easter eggs over the Easter weekend and occasional macarons, in true Paris style. We loved our stay here and will definitely be back again!

Very welcoming staff and generous.
Nice location.
Taj took care of us during breakfast time.
Rooms are always well cleaned.
Breakfast buffet great with wide variety.
We liked our stay and we’ll
Come back surely next time we visit Paris.
***

Everything was great: quiet, cosy, clean rooms, tasty breakfasts, room cleaning every day, free minibar, location… I had a feeling that I was a long-awaited guest. And TJ during breakfasts was very friendly and caring

This hotel was absolutely fantastic! We took a group of 40 on a school World Language trip, including some parents, and everything was spectacular, especially the morning breakfast service facilitated by T.J., who was friendly, funny, provided anything anyone needed - he was simply amazing. This hotel is clean, quaint, extremely quiet, accessible and in the heart of Paris.

We really enjoyed our stay here, what a wonderful hotel and its location is in the 8th district which is just perfect for touring all the main attractions, which are only a short distance from this hotel. With the metro just around the corner.The hotel staff are so friendly and help full, from reception right through to kitchen staff, waiters, to room service / housekeeping staff. The hotel is very clean and well maintained, with a wonderful selection of foods etc.

We do intend to return again soon

We had a nice stay here. The breakfast team was really great. Especially Tej, so friendly and helpful. He even packed us a breakfast package for the day that we wanted to check out early in the morning. Rooms are small which i think is pretty normal in paris. And also the walls are thin, you can here everything.

The staff was kind and helpful, especially the breakfast staff! The food at breakfast was great and everything was clean. Plenty of places to eat dinner around. They have a cute little balcony in the room as well!

an excellent 3 Star hotel and nothing to complain about. The breakfast is very good with a lot of other things to eat. The staff is very friendly and funny. They communicate in different languages. Also a nice add on is the free mini bar in the room which is filled every day an the mini bar in the reception. would come again here if we are in paris.

Thanks to Tej we had a great experience at the breakfast buffet. He was very attentive and kept checking up on us. Great service . The soft bar is really great if you want to have a quick snack.Highly recommend

The breakfast options were excellent and the staff was extremely kind and funny, especially our waiter TJ! The cafeteria also looks stunning and is extremely clean. I came out with a full belly and a wide smile on my face.

Hotel Astoria: Astotel is an excellent place to stay. The location is very convenient. The metro station is within walking distance. A pharmacy and a carrefour store are open until late at night.

We spent four nights in this hotel. The design is modern and unique. The room was nice and clean. In-room fridge drinks are free and replenished daily. The room is big enough for the three of us as I request an extra bed for my son. He likes a free minibar corner with snacks, macarons, and beverages at the hotel lobby services until midnight.

It was a little rainy on the second day, and we planned to go to the Eiffel towel. I walked past the hotel breakfast room in the morning, and the hotel staff name TEJ asked me if I needed any drinks. I didn't say anything then he brought my wife a cup of hot coffee and hot chocolate for my son. Then, he served me a dish full of croissants and said don't be shy. My wife was so amazed as she didn't expect this lovely treat. All I could do was smile back at him and say thank you.

It was about something other than the free food, and I wondered if he knew his kindness and warm welcome gave me my first impression of Paris.

The food and service were fantastic! TJ is the best! He is very kind, always on top of getting us taken care of and making us smile. The hotel itself is very homey, comfortable, and makes for an extremely enjoyable experience. Thank you TJ!

Our time in the hotel has been amazing. Tej, served us in the morning throughout our stay and gave us the best service. He was quick with helping us and picking up our plates. Would definitely come again in the future.

The food was amazing and TJ who helped serve my friends and I was very kind. I enjoyed the variety of snacks that were offered at breakfast and in the evening. TJ and the entire staff were compassionate and welcoming! :) The view from our room and the twisty staircase were all so beautiful.

Tj was very kind and the breakfast was delicious! The service was very good and they speak good English! It’s a beautiful hotel with an amazing view and the room itself has exceeded our expectations! Definitely recommend

Very nice hotel , clean rooms ,centrally located, great staff , Tej Singh restaurant assist was very kind and helpful
I will visit this place again. Even the reception was kind and well mannered
Tej Singh was the best, Breakfast was decent and soft drinks and munching is complimentary

The neighbourhood is not the most pleasant, the hotel street is quiet, it is located at walking distance of Paris centre, a good parking just around the corner, a reasonable breakfast but lady waitress little snobbish. Make sure you get a room on the front side. It is not perfect but ok for a day in Paris.

Welcoming staff and afternoon snacks made this a favorite of the trip. It was great to have an opportunity to chat with the breakfast crew. The beds were blessedly supportive (have been getting saggy beds at some other hotels) and I would stay longer if I could.

Our first time in Paris, France and stayed at Hotel Astoria – Astotel – 75008.

Guess most of the hotels in Paris, are small but Astoria Astotel is full of great service. 3 Star hotel with a 5 Star Service. The hotel room furniture are new and modern. The room is surprisingly clean and neat.

Careful though with the lift (elevator), it’s really small. It can only comfortably fit 2 guests with their luggages :-)

Special thanks to the breakfast team – Kudos to TJ and Merly – who made every guest feel very welcomed. TJ really looked after the guests and made sure that all their needs are provided for. You can really feel the extra care extended – specially to us.

The breakfast has good variety of choices - specially the Quiche Lorraine by their Chef Merly is great!

Special thanks to Rafael too – who patiently accommodated us upon our late check-in and explained all the details of the stay – wow – even the mini-bar is FREE, yes – refilled daily! And coming from a tiring trip around Paris – there is a free snack bar waiting for you at the lobby of the hotel - free flow of coffee, tea, milk, softdrinks, pastries, cakes, chips, etc. We really enjoyed all these privileges!

This hotel is highly recommended! We really had a great time in Paris and it made our stay even more comfortable because we felt safe and secure in our hotel – Astoria Astotel.

The hotel is located within easy walking distance of two Metro stations, but it's slightly away from the main tourist areas. That makes it a little quieter at night - we kept the window opened at night. The highlight, though, was the friendly desk staff and Tej, who managed the tasty breakfast. We welcomed his friendly chats each morning.

The hotel was lovely, all the areas included the room were clean, the staff was amazing and very friendly! The position of the hotel is also very good. Great value and overall the experience was lovely. Highly recommended if you travel on budget.

Not a bad little place to stay, rooms tiny and breakfast is great. Great to be able to pop to sister hotels in Paris and grab a drink. Guy on breakfast was very accommodating not just for service and for all questions asked.Not the same to say with the receptionist and lady at the breakfast which were cold. Good location quite a few restaurants around and shops

The breakfast is great, the rooms are very nice, and the service is very helpful and welcoming ( shoutout TJ- thank you for the breakfast!). The location is very convenient, and is kind of in the perfect spot to see all of Paris.

Hotel Astoria was a great choice for my trip to Paris. It is located between two Metro Stations, making it a great base to tour the city. The room was clean, comfortable, and charming. The staff were helpful and made checkin/out an easy process.

Breakfast, an additional E12 charge, was delicious and had a nice variety. Pal, the gentleman who helped serve breakfast , was kind and funny.

Overall, my stay was wonderful and I would plan on staying at this location again next time I'm in Paris, which will hopefully be soon!

Great hotel and amazing, very welcoming staff! Room was clean, warm and specious enough for three people. Very smooth service, truly nothing to complain about. Public transport is also closed to the hotel. Special thanks goes to Tej for providing great breakfast service!

The hotel was okay. It was modernly updated.The room was dated and very small but clean. The bathroom was nicely updated. We got upset at breakfast lady in red that served saying Breakfast was not open yet before 7 but we needed to go out early but she didnt open it but the waiter served us. what is needed to fill us up. They were late snacks thats offered and the receptionist were welcoming.

Lovely hotel with spacious, clean rooms, hidden away on a Rue de Moscou in the Montmarte area.

Walking distance to sights such Sacre Coure and Opera Garnier. Alternatively 2 easy to reach metro stops with links to many tourist sights.

We were a family of 3 and had a fab triple room with a balcony, which caught the afternoon sun.

We didn’t sample breakfast here but we did make use of the snacks and drinks, which was ideal with a little one.

Staff were friendly and accommodating, offering advice on places to eat and how to reach the nearby sights.

We would highly recommend this property.

The cafe restaurant is very delicious!!
He’s name is Sings he very kind and always take care and bring a lot of food.
Room is very clean and nice all people so nice.
I would like to come back again this hotel.

A very nice and clean hotel. Excellent location at 3 minutes walking distance of the Rome metro station. The staff is very helpful (specially Pal). A particularly good buffet breakfast under a glass dome. The cakes and refreshments available until 1 am in any hotel of the chain are certainly a big plus

Le petit déjeuner est magnifique.
The breakfast here was awesome.
ホテルの朝食は、サービスも充実しており、最高でした。
Merci beaucoup, TEJ.
Thank you very much for your full services.
TEJさんのサービスは、とても親切で、快適に過ごすことができました。
外国人にも人気で、英語にも対応しており、また宿泊したいと思いました。
À bientôt 👋

Nice staff, the nicest breakfast guy in all trip !!
Nice location ! A walk distance to restaurants and Sacre Couer. 200 letters! Wow trip advisor , make things easyer for us !! Would really appreciate

Had a very pleasant stay at hotel astoria, Staff very nice and helpful, food excellent as we're the kitchen staff, would definetly recommend, Paris is a beautiful city to visit, Hotel a little bit away from sites but got to use de buses

We stayed 2 nights in Astoria hotel and it was a great stay. The location is perfect- metro, market, everything is around. It’s very quiet. The breakfast is awesome, it has a lot of choices. I recommend it!

This place is perfect. From the moment you come in, reception is very welcoming, explain everything super well. Rooms are nice and clean and breakfast is delicious, everything is fresh and Tj the server is very attentive and friendly. Overall a very good family place to stay.

Great location, great rooms, great breakfast, all in all a great experience. I particularly enjoyed Tej, he was very accommodating at breakfast particularly with my niece and nephew. Raphael was also very kind and friendly.

Great stay at a comfortable hotel! We loved the neighborhood and enjoyed breakfast every morning with Tej! The food was delicious and very welcome after my bad jet lag :) the rooms were comfortable - I will say, the bed was a little firm for my liking but I prefer a softer bed. But overall, this place was a great value for the cost. We easily got to several different subway lines and the staff was so friendly and helpful! :)

We stayed in Paris 3 days for businnes. In Hotel Astoria we found all we needed: a lot of usefull services, a central position, good prices and a very kind staff. We will certainly came back! Thanks for all!

Really enjoyed this hotel. It's close to the subways and not far from hotspots in Paris. The breakfast is good with great service and special shout out to our guy Tej for making our breakfast a more friendly affair.

Rooms are comfortable and clean. Comes with a nice little fridge too. Overall would recommend this place very much.

I stayed in Astoria for a week. It was very comfortable, quiet, staff is friendly. Breakfast was good. Staff member, Tej, was very nice, accommodating, answering all the questions and giving great suggestions of the places to visit!!!
Hotel is very close to the metro. Plenty of shops and restaurants around.
Would stay there again.

The staff are nice. Tez is especially kind.
He made me feel good and had fun when I ate breakfast.
It was nice that other employees greeted me with a smile.
I am willing to come to this hotel next time I come.

Me and tej had a goodtime! He is approachable person. If you guys go here in astoria hotel better look for tej is so nice person! And our room is so clean and the morning breakfast is good and clean tej is so friendly

It is a charming hotel, and the service is fantastic. And Especially meeting our new friend Taj was a cherry on top. he is very kind and very helpful especially when it came to knowledge about the city. he set us up right and gave us some awesome advice.

Great atmosphere and location. Comfortable rooms for a quick layover in Paris. staff was very friendly and all spoke great English. Tej was a great host and very accommodating. He made me feel very welcomed. Thank you.

Recommended Hotel. Only 2min to train bay walk. All staff are friendly. Good and complete breakfast.
Especially good service from Tej, Marlyn, Arleen 🥰.
A lit of restaurant nearby with good taste.
Love to come back here

This hotel was easy to get to, the metro stop Rome is about 5min walk away. Room was cosy and comfortable.

Beds a lot lower to ground than I’m used to. Pillows were quite hard, which suited me fine but mum prefers hers a bit softer.

Breakfast was lovely, very plentiful and loads of tables for everyone to sit.

This hotel has a little snack table in the foyer that is free for anyone, I loved their chocolate rice cakes. They have a few hotels is Paris and anyone staying could go into any of the other hotel for snacks, we didn’t use that, too much to see in Paris.

The day we left Paris, all public transport was on strike, the reception had put a sign up, so we knew in advance there would be an issue, reception booked a taxi for us to get back to airport well in advance.

It’s my third time in Paris, and my second time staying at this hotel. The room was uniquely quaint, and the staff was extremely warm and friendly. Big thanks to Tej for the hospitality and jokes! I’ll definitely be back.

Tej’s enthusiasm made my first time in Paris amazing! Our breakfast had a delightful surprise when I walked in to see Tej. Coming from the US, this hotel gave us a nice welcome and Tej was a big reason for that!

Really lovely hotel with friendly staff, especially TEJ is making me happy every morning with his enthousiasme!! Would love to go back tho :) thanks a lot! Also the street of the hotel was beautiful!!

The hotel was okay, small rooms and hard beds but clean and nice central location. Tej, the server in the dining room was fantastic. Efficient and super fun. He kept all the guests entertained by making them guess where he was originally from. Great guy and keep it up.

The hotel was perfect for our family. The rooms were clean and newly remodeled. Breakfast was amazing and Tej was an excellent host. Rooms included free drinks and the snack station was a hit with the kids! Will plan on coming back

It was my first time at this hotel and I really enjoyed my stay. The workers are really the friendliest people waiting to help you with whatever you need. Arlene and Merly were amazing and so helpful in the am buffet. The front desk people are also such a pleasure helping you with your travel questions. Highly recommend to stay here!

We stayed here for 1 night. It was a small room with window facing the street. The hotel itself is tucked away in a small lane, but it is so conveniently located very close to Rome metro station. It is just a 3 minute walk to the station. That was a big plus for us. Don't expect large corridors or walk ways leading to the room. Lift is also very small. But they have tried to make best use of the available space given the expensive real estate in Paris. The rooms are tightly packed and the doors of adjacent room is only inches away. But still once inside the room, it is quite private, nice and cozy. The buffet breakfast was excellent with generous spread. Manager Tej was pleasant and friendly with everyone engaging in small conversations that made them feel welcome in the place.

Astotel hotel is a very good value for your money. It’s a nice room, clean, staff is really friendly, and location is good. Tej, the lovely employee in the am at breakfast is also a highlight. I had him for 2 mornings at the hotel and he is so pleasant and friendly. He would start the day of great for us with his positive energy and friendliness. Overall very happy with our stay and you won’t be disappointed if you stay here!!!! Thank you again to Tej and the rest of the staff!

Great location and facilities for 3 star Hotel this is the best hotel i have ever stayed. Room was clean and love the mini bar complimentary non-alcoholic drinks also Lounge service with free snacks and drinks.

Nice breakfast and the staff at the breakfast also super helpful, Tej. He welcoming us as a family traveler and so friendly.
Over all good choice and nice deal! ❤❤

Had a lovely stay here, will definitely be back! Staff very friendly and happy to help and housekeeping amazing! Free snacks and drinks during the day is ideal and just steps away from the metro. Couldn’t ask for more!

Thanks guys :)

We love having breakfast in this hotel, the food was execellent and the workers are fantastic, specially Tej.
The room is nice, a bit small but very clean.
They have also some snacks during the evenig for free: apples, biscuits, etc
We love it!!!

The hotel is super cute and the staff was fabulous. Tej was the best and even opened up early for us at breakfast when we had jet lag. Great location for getting around Paris. Would highly recommend this hotel. Daily cleaning, friendly and safe.

Great hotel that was clean, friendly and the breakfast was amazing! The breakfast host (Tej) saw I was peeking around the breakfast area earlier than when they ipened and offered me coffee and even opened the breakfast area up early for my wife and I. I cant say enough kind things about him.

Our Stay in Hotel Astoria was very nice for our trip. Hotel was clean and always very accommodating for the group. Breakfast was excellent with fresh fruit, juices, and meats daily. Tej was there daily in the morning to help with breakfast in any way he could. He was always polite and pleasant to see in the morning. I appreciate starting the day with him. We were very happy as a group to stay with this hotel throughout our time in Paris

We really enjoyed our 2nd visit at this hotel. The staff is very helpful. The rooms are quiet, and we loved our balcony! The Astotel chain is great because of all the extra amenities offered. We hope to return.

Hotel is near by Rome station. The room is cosy and facillity of hotel is suitable.
Most of all, Staff Tej is really nice and helpful. If we travel to Paris again, we will be back here. The room is clean, and breakfast included was delicious. We had a a good meal here.
